commit_message: update header to unify with Clair3

*v0.6 (April 25, 2023)*: Upgraded Python 3.6 to 3.9. Upgraded Whatshap to [v1.7](https://github.com/HKU-BAL/Clair3/issues/193). Fix gVCF format [error](https://github.com/HKU-BAL/Clair3-Trio/issues/3). Added and [fixed](https://github.com/HKU-BAL/Clair3-Trio/issues/4) "--enable_phasing" support. and "--enable_output_phasing" and "enable_output_haplotagging" supports.
update to v0.3, speed is as 2.2 times for individual

V0.1 r7
replace float integer by string for comparison
file command not exist in docker envrionment, replace with gvcf compression detect
change PRO and REF_PRO to integer

fix splitting validation data issue, added buffers for random_validation, logic remains the same for using validation_fn option
also remove intermediate files in pileup_only calling mode
add remove_intermediate_dir option to allow remove intermediate directory, including intermediate phased BAM, pileup and full-alignment results
compress intermediate GVCF output using lz4, and bgzip final merge_out.gvcf
